        <div class="case-study-family">
            <h3>üìã Case Study: Local Family Archive - 150 Years of History</h3>
            <p><strong>Project:</strong> Comprehensive digitization and restoration of a local family archive spanning five generations, from Civil War era tintypes to 1990s color photographs.</p>

            <p><strong>Archive Contents:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>1,247 family photographs ranging from 1870s to 1990s</li>
                <li>156 glass plate negatives from early 1900s</li>
                <li>423 35mm color slides from 1960s-1980s</li>
                <li>78 damaged photographs requiring extensive restoration</li>
                <li>12 family albums with deteriorating pages</li>
                <li>Mixed formats including tintypes, cabinet cards, and Polaroids</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>Restoration Challenges:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Civil War era tintype with severe corrosion and missing corners</li>
                <li>1920s wedding portrait with water damage and torn sections</li>
                <li>Color slides with severe color shifts and mold damage</li>
                <li>Glass plate negatives with cracks and emulsion loss</li>
                <li>Mixed organizational systems spanning multiple generations</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>Our Comprehensive Solution:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>High-resolution scanning at 600-4000 DPI based on original format</li>
                <li>Professional restoration of 78 damaged photographs</li>
                <li>Color correction and enhancement for faded family memories</li>
                <li>Chronological organization with genealogical family tree integration</li>
                <li>Creation of digital family timeline spanning 150 years</li>
                <li>Multiple delivery formats including cloud storage and physical media</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>Result:</strong> Complete digital preservation of family history, 1,900+ high-resolution digital images, restored family treasures, organized genealogical archive, and ongoing digital preservation plan.</p>

